# Template Literals ðŸ“œ

Backticks (` `) allow variables in strings.

```javascript
const name = "Alice";
const age = 25;

// Old
console.log("User " + name + " is " + age);

// ES6
console.log(`User ${name} is ${age}`);
```

Also supports multi-line strings!

# Destructuring âœ‚ï¸

Unpack values from arrays or objects easily.

```javascript
// Object
const user = { name: "Bob", role: "Admin" };
const { name, role } = user;
console.log(role); // "Admin"

// Array
const rgb = [255, 0, 0];
const [red, green, blue] = rgb;
```
